\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 4. Frequently Asked Questions
\par 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 Older versions of ignitionServer were a bit easier to use/modify than this current version. This
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 version is MUCH more powerful, has more than enough commands to be useful, and is quite a bit
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 less buggy. Please make sure you r\hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 ead this FAQ before you post to the support tracker.
\par 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 Q: When I start ignitionServer, nothing comes up!
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 A: It's supposed to do this! ignitionServer now runs as a full-fledged daemon. You will not get
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1    any interface at all (unless you are on Windows NT an\hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 d you installed the ignitionServer
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1    Monitor). If you are not sure you started it properly, start your IRC client and type:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1      /server localhost
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1    If you connect to something, the server is running. A less time-intensive method would be to
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1    hit Ctrl-\hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 Alt-Del and see if the ignitionServer process is running.
\par 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 Q: Why doesn't ignitionServer start?
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 A: First, make sure you read the above question. Then, check the following things:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1    1) Is ircx.conf in the same folder as ignitionServer?
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1    2) Did I modify i\hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 rcx.conf improperly?
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1    3) Is ircx.conf named properly (it must be ircx.conf -- do not capitalize the extension or any
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1       other part of the name!)?
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1    If you diagnosed those things and still have a problem, make sure ignitionServer isn't running
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1    as a\hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 nother process (Ctrl-Alt-Del). ignitionServer will only start one time. All other times it
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1    will not allow it. 
\par 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 Q: ignitionServer sends out Closing Link: (AutoKilled: Server Misconfigured) and disconnects users on 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1     connection
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 A: A new feature was in\hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 troduced to stop incorrectly configured servers to be used_(E.G. Using Default 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1     A Lines). To disable this feature simply find X:DIE in ircx.conf file and change the 1 to a 0
\par 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 Q: What operating system is recommended to run ignitionServer?
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 A: We recommend you use Windows NT 4, Windows 2000, Windows XP, or Windows Server 2003. Windows
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1    95/98/ME is not recommended at all.
\par 
