\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 A: To be honest NONE except that they both can be given different on-join-modes.
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1     To give a on-join-mode for P use
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1       X:HIGHPROT:[Q|O|V|NORM]
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1     To give a on-join-mode for p \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1 use
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af23\loch\f1       X:LOWPROT:[Q|O|V|NORM]
